# Version Management

## Version Format

`MAJOR.MINOR.BUILD.REVISION` — e.g. `0.0.0.1`, `1.0.0.0`, `1.2.3.45`

| Part | When to increment |
|------|------------------|
| MAJOR | Breaking change / incompatible API |
| MINOR | New feature, backwards-compatible |
| BUILD | Bug fix |
| REVISION | Internal/patch |

## plcproj Version

Set in `.plcproj` `<PropertyGroup>`:

```xml
<ProjectVersion>0.0.0.1</ProjectVersion>
```

## Global_Version GVL

Create `GVLs/Global_Version.TcGVL` with `ST_LibVersion` from `Tc2_System`:

```iecst
{attribute 'TcGenerated'}
VAR_GLOBAL CONSTANT
    stLibVersion : ST_LibVersion := (
        iMajor    := 0,
        iMinor    := 0,
        iBuild    := 0,
        iRevision := 1,
        sVersion  := '0.0.0.1'
    );
END_VAR
```

`ST_LibVersion` is defined in `Tc2_System`. Reference it for runtime version queries.

## Project Folder Convention

```
Versions/
  0.0.0.1/
    changelog-0.0.0.1.md
  1.0.0.0/
    changelog-1.0.0.0.md
```

## Changelog Format

For detailed changelog writing instructions, templates, and real examples, use the `twincat3-changelog` skill (`.cursor/skills/twincat3-changelog/SKILL.md`).

Key rules:
- English only
- One file per version in `Versions/X.X.X.X/changelog-X.X.X.X.md`
- Major releases: `# Changelog — Tc3_IoT_BA X.X.X.X` with Added/Changed/Fixed/Deprecated
- Bug fix releases: `## Version X.X.X.X – Title` with categorized sections
- Breaking changes use `> [!CAUTION]` blocks
- Code examples use `iecst` syntax highlighting
- No implementation details — purpose and impact only
